participate\/developers\/\">xtuml.org\/participate\/developers\/<\/a><\/p>\n<p>If you want to join the xtUML Community as a developer (of BridgePoint and xtUML models), there is a &#8216;Developer Getting Started&#8217; guide that walks you step by step through building the tool.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Social Media:<\/strong><br \/>\nFollow <a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/showcase\/4800651\/\">xtUML.org on LinkedIn<\/a>.<br \/>\nJoin the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/groups\/1889066\">Executable UML discussion group on LinkedIn<\/a>.<br \/>\nFollow\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/onefactinc\/\">One Fact on facebook<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Professionally delivered training and consulting is available from One Fact and others.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The richest source of information about xtUML is found on xtuml.org. Specifically, there is a &#8216;Learn&#8217; menu item with all kinds of resources. Books: xtuml.org\/learn\/books\/ For a high-level overview, I recommend MDA Distilled. For deeper Executable UML, I recommend Mellor\/Balcer and then Rastrick. Articles: xtuml.org\/learn\/articles\/ Training Course: An interactive online training course is available that [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":1369,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-826","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-uncategorized"],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/onefact.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/info-8161710.png","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/onefact.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/826","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/onefact.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/onefact.net\/wp-json\/wp\